1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,580
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,580 --> 00:00:03,069
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,300
(Episode 28)

4
00:00:06,300 --> 00:00:07,882
You know there are rumors going around...

5
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:10,877
about the two of you
in the planning office, right?

6
00:00:11,846 --> 00:00:13,914
Rumors?

7
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:18,184
That's absolutely not true.

8
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:22,487
I'm just working with the Team Manager
as part of the same team.

9
00:00:22,896 --> 00:00:26,233
Even last night's all-nighter
was completely unintentional.

10
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:27,694
If such rumors are going around,

11
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:30,773
don't you think there might be
something wrong with your behavior?

12
00:00:31,027 --> 00:00:32,366
Manager Seo...

13
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:35,735
I acknowledge
that Joy is an excellent program.

14
00:00:36,290 --> 00:00:38,004
That's why, even as an intern,

15
00:00:38,501 --> 00:00:41,742
everyone has treated you
like a full-time employee.

16
00:00:42,344 --> 00:00:44,378
You've been given special treatment
as Joy's developer.

17
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:46,333
I'm aware of that.

18
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,667
And I'm grateful
for how everyone's treated me,

19
00:00:49,040 --> 00:00:50,651
especially you, Manager Seo.

20
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:55,055
You might just spend six months here,
kill some time, and leave,

21
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,223
but the Team Manager won't.

22
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:59,500
Think about how your careless actions...

23
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:02,563
could affect the Team Manager
before you act.

24
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:05,067
About my careless actions...

25
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:09,937
Could you tell me specifically
what you mean?

26
00:01:10,802 --> 00:01:12,639
I honestly don't get it.

27
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:14,107
I need to know in order to correct it.

28
00:01:15,507 --> 00:01:17,992
I'm talking about this specific attitude.

29
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:20,747
Saying whatever you want,
acting on impulse,

30
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:22,813
not caring about those around you,

31
00:01:23,747 --> 00:01:26,219
and being overly true
to your own emotions.

32
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,266
I'm sorry to say this,

33
00:01:28,834 --> 00:01:30,057
but just because it's a big company...

34
00:01:30,420 --> 00:01:33,853
doesn't mean you shouldn't be true
to your feelings.

35
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,263
As long as I'm not neglecting my work...

36
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,600
or harming the team...

37
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:42,000
Don't you think
the fact that such rumors are spreading...

38
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,504
right before the competition
is hurting team morale?

39
00:01:45,873 --> 00:01:48,707
If I've harmed the team,
I sincerely apologize.

40
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:54,647
But if those rumors are based solely
on my attitude or behavior,

41
00:01:55,359 --> 00:01:59,059
wouldn't the Team Manager have shown
that he was uncomfortable first?

42
00:01:59,467 --> 00:02:00,467
What did you say?

43
00:02:02,501 --> 00:02:05,167
The Team Manager hasn't taken issue
with my behavior.

44
00:02:05,767 --> 00:02:08,367
So I can't help
but think your repeated comments...

45
00:02:09,327 --> 00:02:13,433
are due to some personal feelings
between the two of you.

46
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,005
So what the Team Manager said before
was right.

47
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,440
- Sorry?
- This isn't...

48
00:02:20,533 --> 00:02:23,767
a playground where you can run wild
as you please.

49
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:25,220
Understood?

50
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:33,433
I...

51
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:36,489
really gave it my all.

52
00:02:37,279 --> 00:02:39,559
Like any parent,

53
00:02:40,090 --> 00:02:42,600
I raised my kids thinking...

54
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:47,167
I could give everything for their success.

55
00:02:48,147 --> 00:02:49,369
But now,

56
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:53,306
they say they're struggling because of me.

57
00:02:54,367 --> 00:02:58,779
They say I ruined their lives.

58
00:02:59,027 --> 00:03:00,027
Wait.

59
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:02,714
Isn't that a bit of an exaggeration?

60
00:03:02,714 --> 00:03:04,480
There's no way the kids in your family...

61
00:03:06,167 --> 00:03:10,137
would be so disrespectful.

62
00:03:10,137 --> 00:03:12,793
She's right.
Eun Hyeong, Eun Ae, and Eun Nim...

63
00:03:12,793 --> 00:03:14,127
would never think that.

64
00:03:14,127 --> 00:03:17,564
Even if they don't say it outright,
they all think it deep down.

65
00:03:18,268 --> 00:03:20,967
Because of me, because of my expectations,

66
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:22,798
they couldn't live the way they wanted.

67
00:03:23,426 --> 00:03:26,873
Now, they want to live their own lives!

68
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:28,642
Then let them!

69
00:03:28,642 --> 00:03:29,876
Once you've raised them that much,

70
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:32,742
of course they should live on their own!

71
00:03:32,742 --> 00:03:34,881
Exactly!

72
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:42,823
But what's been weighing on you so much...

73
00:03:43,586 --> 00:03:45,992
that you wanted to go all out
with me today?

74
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,574
Go on, tell me everything.

75
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:53,667
I had her mom...

76
00:03:53,667 --> 00:03:55,809
when I was 23,

77
00:03:55,809 --> 00:03:58,067
and I was on my own by 30.

78
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,640
Here she goes again.

79
00:04:00,776 --> 00:04:05,967
I struggled alone in the marketplace
to raise her,

80
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:10,851
and she ended up pregnant
before she was even married.

81
00:04:10,851 --> 00:04:11,917
Grandma!

82
00:04:11,918 --> 00:04:14,988
Why are you shouting like that?

83
00:04:15,174 --> 00:04:17,414
I told you to stop bringing that up.

84
00:04:17,414 --> 00:04:20,494
But that's the core of my story.

85
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:26,419
Is there a hole in this?

86
00:04:26,419 --> 00:04:28,902
Did the makgeolli leak out?

87
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:35,067
This really is the last bottle, okay?

88
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:37,177
Got it, the last!

89
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,712
This is the last bottle, ma'am!

90
00:04:40,014 --> 00:04:41,014
Okay.

91
00:04:41,301 --> 00:04:43,017
No, from now on,

92
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:45,051
should I call you "Ms. Park,"

93
00:04:45,714 --> 00:04:47,187
not "ma'am?"

94
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:49,433
Or just "sis?"

95
00:04:49,433 --> 00:04:50,533
Sis?

96
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:54,467
Hey, that sounds nice.

97
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:57,900
I like it.

98
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,484
My dear sister!

99
00:05:01,894 --> 00:05:03,258
Wait...

100
00:05:08,342 --> 00:05:09,342
Ji Seon...

101
00:05:16,516 --> 00:05:18,752
What's wrong, Mom? Are you upset?

102
00:05:19,147 --> 00:05:20,233
What happened?

103
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,155
What were you doing there with Dad?

104
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:26,726
Dad said we should go hand out balloons.

105
00:05:29,262 --> 00:05:30,597
(Children's Writing Institute)

106
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,233
I'm sorry, Ji Seon.

107
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,741
I never meant for you
to find out like this.

108
00:05:42,589 --> 00:05:45,967
I got a job
at the children's writing institute...

109
00:05:45,967 --> 00:05:47,467
in that shopping center,
full-time, five days a week.

110
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:49,749
I should've told you right away,

111
00:05:50,567 --> 00:05:53,697
but I couldn't bring myself
to disappoint you when you were so happy.

112
00:05:54,598 --> 00:05:57,257
Are you seriously calling that an excuse?

113
00:05:57,257 --> 00:05:59,926
Mom, Dad, you're not fighting, right?

114
00:06:00,139 --> 00:06:02,161
We're supposed to have a party today.

115
00:06:02,847 --> 00:06:04,798
A party, right!

116
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:08,301
Honey, let's keep our promise
to Bit Na first...

117
00:06:08,567 --> 00:06:10,236
It's always like this, every time.

118
00:06:10,353 --> 00:06:13,020
When you're cornered,
you use Bit Na as an excuse and dodge it.

119
00:06:14,567 --> 00:06:15,567
Mom!

120
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:19,767
I'll be in my room meditating.

121
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:22,773
We have a party, so please make up.

122
00:06:23,493 --> 00:06:24,493
All right, Bit Na.

123
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:27,153
Don't worry. Just trust your dad.

124
00:06:27,456 --> 00:06:29,389
- Okay, I trust you.
- Yeah.

125
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:38,831
I don't want to fight
in front of Bit Na anymore.

126
00:06:39,292 --> 00:06:41,968
I'll be at my parents' house for a while.

127
00:06:42,407 --> 00:06:44,243
Tell Bit Na I went on a long trip.

128
00:06:44,243 --> 00:06:47,067
No, that's not the right way
to handle this.

129
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:48,433
Wait.

130
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:54,247
Can't you try to understand me? I just...

131
00:06:55,946 --> 00:06:56,946
Fine.

132
00:06:57,633 --> 00:07:00,386
I got carried away hearing
"full-time position"...

133
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:03,367
and assumed it was a university job,

134
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,200
so you couldn't bring yourself to say it.

135
00:07:05,546 --> 00:07:08,728
Fine, I'll try to understand that part.

136
00:07:09,134 --> 00:07:12,800
But why did you have Bit Na
standing on the street,

137
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,800
handing out flyers like that?

138
00:07:15,286 --> 00:07:17,103
Why was she there?

139
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:20,506
I called Mom to ask her to watch Bit Na,
but she didn't answer.

140
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:24,577
Do you know how embarrassed
and flustered I was earlier?

141
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:27,513
Especially in front of my junior!

142
00:07:27,783 --> 00:07:30,167
I was just working hard
as the head of the family.

143
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:32,800
Is that really something
to be so ashamed of?

144
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,821
Yes, it is.

145
00:07:35,340 --> 00:07:38,758
You might be confident, but I'm mortified!

146
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:40,225
Move.

147
00:07:40,933 --> 00:07:42,133
Honey!

148
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:46,986
Mom, Dad,
I finished setting up for the party.

149
00:07:46,986 --> 00:07:48,068
Come quickly.

150
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:52,172
Please, honey.

151
00:08:04,884 --> 00:08:06,987
(Professor Cho Eun Hyeong)

152
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:16,486
Dad, shouldn't we light the candles now?

153
00:08:41,493 --> 00:08:43,589
It's nice and open out here.

154
00:08:44,275 --> 00:08:46,673
Team Manager, what brings you here?

155
00:08:46,673 --> 00:08:49,362
With the competition coming up,
is it okay for the intern to be this idle?

156
00:08:50,267 --> 00:08:52,031
I'm sorry, I'll head back right away.

157
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:57,233
Team Manager, I have something to say.

158
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:58,467
Yes, go ahead.

159
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:03,700
I think Manager Seo gravely misunderstood
the two of us.

160
00:09:04,793 --> 00:09:07,093
I'll be more careful from now on,

161
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,015
but please be careful too.

162
00:09:09,015 --> 00:09:11,067
What exactly should I be careful about?

163
00:09:11,067 --> 00:09:12,467
What did we even do?

164
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:13,953
Exactly.

165
00:09:14,826 --> 00:09:17,223
But maybe it doesn't look that way
to others.

166
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:20,293
The slippers, the all-nighter...

167
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:23,867
The all-nighter was just because of work
for the competition.

168
00:09:24,167 --> 00:09:25,898
The slippers? I won't wear them...

169
00:09:26,293 --> 00:09:28,193
since it seems to bother you.

170
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:32,338
Is there really something wrong
with my behavior?

171
00:09:33,326 --> 00:09:35,175
You do tend to run wild.

172
00:09:35,513 --> 00:09:37,677
Like a ball that could bounce anywhere.

173
00:09:38,126 --> 00:09:41,800
Did you overhear my conversation
with Manager Seo?

174
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:44,951
But I don't mind your behavior.

175
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:47,790
- Sorry?
- I'm fine with it.

176
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:50,156
You can run wild all you want on my turf.

177
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:54,927
Team Manager...

178
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:56,933
Perhaps...

179
00:09:57,433 --> 00:09:58,900
Perhaps what?

180
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,167
Do you like me?

181
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:03,903
What?

182
00:10:06,293 --> 00:10:08,343
How did your thoughts go there?

183
00:10:08,820 --> 00:10:11,113
When I said you could run wild on my turf,

184
00:10:11,113 --> 00:10:13,446
I meant you could work freely on the team.

185
00:10:13,765 --> 00:10:15,332
Like you? Who would like whom?

186
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,400
Right?

187
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:19,074
What a relief. That scared me.

188
00:10:22,153 --> 00:10:24,257
I just thought, maybe you did.

189
00:10:25,726 --> 00:10:27,093
And that text message too.

190
00:10:27,565 --> 00:10:28,661
"Dream of me."

191
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,898
You saw that?

192
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,100
Darn it.

193
00:10:36,467 --> 00:10:39,369
I deleted it right away,
but what happened was...

194
00:10:39,369 --> 00:10:42,842
I was replying
to your "good night" message,

195
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:44,010
and by mistake...

196
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:46,279
Why would "dream of me"
be a reply to "good night?"

197
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,648
Anyway,
I'm so relieved that's not the case.

198
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:54,067
What are you so relieved about?

199
00:10:54,826 --> 00:10:56,623
Don't stay away from your desk too long.
Get back in.

200
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:58,086
We have no time for this.

201
00:10:59,025 --> 00:11:01,321
What? Why is he angry?

202
00:11:02,313 --> 00:11:03,429
Team Manager!

203
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:10,500
Manager Seo seemed like
she hadn't eaten lunch, so I bought this.

204
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,872
Could you give it to her?

205
00:11:13,433 --> 00:11:16,175
Don't say I bought it. Absolutely not.

206
00:11:31,267 --> 00:11:33,826
Manager Seo,
can I speak with you for a moment?

207
00:11:34,847 --> 00:11:36,596
Yes...

208
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,099
(Nature Porridge)

209
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,367
What is this?

210
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,705
You skipped lunch, right? Eat it.

211
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,811
Gyeol, I have something to tell you.

212
00:11:52,353 --> 00:11:53,667
I have something to say too.

213
00:11:53,667 --> 00:11:56,282
Let's talk after the competition.

214
00:11:56,749 --> 00:11:57,749
Enjoy your meal.

215
00:12:04,791 --> 00:12:06,893
(Nature Porridge)

216
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:09,095
Manager, you're out here.

217
00:12:09,095 --> 00:12:10,830
(Nature Porridge)

218
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,233
Did she buy this porridge for me?

219
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:32,117
Who do you think you are,
hurting my daughter for over ten years?

220
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,533
Hey, it's me.

221
00:12:44,533 --> 00:12:45,567
Hello, Mother.

222
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:47,967
What brings you to call me like this?

223
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:50,570
Come by the house this weekend.
Let's have a meal together.

224
00:12:50,860 --> 00:12:54,200
Of course. Just call me anytime,
and I'll come running.

225
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,808
What's wrong with you?

226
00:12:56,466 --> 00:12:58,944
Why can't you even win over
a woman's heart?

227
00:12:59,581 --> 00:13:00,947
This is so frustrating.

228
00:13:01,681 --> 00:13:04,484
I'm sorry, Mother. I'll try harder.

229
00:13:04,751 --> 00:13:05,933
Anyway, come home.

230
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:07,720
I'll step in more actively myself.

231
00:13:08,979 --> 00:13:09,979
Thank you, Mother.

232
00:13:11,714 --> 00:13:12,714
Yes!

233
00:13:12,714 --> 00:13:13,933
Scalpel, suction!

234
00:13:14,121 --> 00:13:15,461
Blood pressure is dropping.

235
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,096
Blood pressure is dropping!

236
00:13:17,895 --> 00:13:20,433
You're raising my blood pressure!

237
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:28,387
Did I eat something wrong
when I was pregnant with him?

238
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:32,741
Internal bleeding has started again.

239
00:13:32,741 --> 00:13:34,247
Bleeding!

240
00:13:34,247 --> 00:13:37,050
Dispatch the doctor helicopter!

241
00:13:41,067 --> 00:13:42,300
This is so fun.

242
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:44,757
So fun!

243
00:13:44,757 --> 00:13:45,853
So fun!

244
00:13:45,853 --> 00:13:47,093
That startled me.

245
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:50,833
How am I supposed to wait
until the next episode?

246
00:13:56,367 --> 00:13:59,130
Crazy Anne, did you read
the new "The ER Witch" episode?

247
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:01,774
This one is amazing too.

248
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,145
You've already read it, ER King?

249
00:14:06,279 --> 00:14:09,649
Of course. I've been waiting forever
for it to be uploaded.

250
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:13,353
Crazy Anne,
are you really not close to the author?

251
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,333
How did you know
the series would continue?

252
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:17,990
No, I'm not close to them at all.

253
00:14:19,153 --> 00:14:21,786
I just trust the author.

254
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:25,633
But isn't "The ER Witch"
getting a webtoon adaptation?

255
00:14:26,033 --> 00:14:28,601
These days,
every popular novel gets adapted.

256
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:32,438
Wouldn't it be a huge hit as a webtoon?

257
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,509
There are no plans
for a webtoon adaptation yet.

258
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:40,433
What?
I thought you weren't close to the author.

259
00:14:40,433 --> 00:14:43,249
How do you know there are no plans?

260
00:14:44,347 --> 00:14:47,554
As an avid reader, I just have a feeling.

261
00:14:48,867 --> 00:14:50,764
I'm busy, so I'll get going.

262
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:55,294
"I'll get going?"

263
00:14:57,460 --> 00:14:59,193
Why does that feel so familiar?

264
00:15:01,126 --> 00:15:02,126
No way...

265
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:05,772
Is Crazy Anne "Oh My Oz?"

266
00:15:06,105 --> 00:15:08,775
(Cancer diet?
It could be the worst choice.)

267
00:15:12,461 --> 00:15:14,399
Where on earth did it go?

268
00:15:14,399 --> 00:15:16,399
It's not like earrings grow legs.

269
00:15:18,347 --> 00:15:19,519
Sit down.

270
00:15:19,967 --> 00:15:20,967
Sorry?

271
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:22,588
Okay.

272
00:15:25,793 --> 00:15:28,060
Why do you keep searching our room?

273
00:15:28,347 --> 00:15:32,065
What? What do you mean...

274
00:15:33,835 --> 00:15:34,901
Then what is this?

275
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,038
Why is this with you...

276
00:15:39,180 --> 00:15:40,180
Tell me.

277
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,100
Why do you keep searching our room?

278
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:44,877
Well, actually...

279
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:48,233
Min Ho's dad and the safe...

280
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:49,367
What?

281
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,885
You went through our room with him?

282
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,733
No, we didn't mean to.

283
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:58,500
Last time, it seemed like Father...

284
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,459
didn't know what that necklace was either,

285
00:16:01,040 --> 00:16:04,230
so I was just curious,
and Dae Chi went along with it for a bit.

286
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:07,067
You people, honestly...

287
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:10,102
Mother, I'm sorry. I won't do it again.

288
00:16:13,559 --> 00:16:17,376
Please, just don't tell Father.

289
00:16:26,419 --> 00:16:28,401
I'm going nuts!

290
00:16:28,401 --> 00:16:30,307
Why did I drop this?

291
00:16:30,307 --> 00:16:31,307
What do I do?

292
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,566
Did you sleep well?

293
00:16:34,260 --> 00:16:36,826
I feel refreshed after a short nap.

294
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:41,200
Shall we go out to the yard
and get some sunlight?

295
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:42,867
Yes, let's do that.

296
00:16:43,486 --> 00:16:46,398
Mother, should I come with you?

297
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:47,933
No need.

298
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,867
We'll just take a quick walk
around the garden and come back.

299
00:16:54,006 --> 00:16:56,282
This is bad. What if she tells Father?

300
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:05,858
Honey, this is serious!

301
00:17:06,547 --> 00:17:07,547
What?

302
00:17:07,867 --> 00:17:10,429
You need to somehow keep Mother quiet.

303
00:17:11,499 --> 00:17:14,366
If she finds out we touched Father's safe,
we're done for.

304
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:20,406
Wrong number.

305
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,443
When did you get here?

306
00:17:24,443 --> 00:17:25,444
Father.

307
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,974
Did you touch Grandpa's safe that night?

308
00:17:27,974 --> 00:17:29,800
What nonsense.

309
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,266
When would I ever?

310
00:17:31,266 --> 00:17:32,866
What's wrong with you?

311
00:17:33,287 --> 00:17:35,321
Why do you keep disappointing me?

312
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,156
Disappointing?

313
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,825
How dare you say that to your dad?

314
00:17:40,433 --> 00:17:41,600
And you.

315
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,395
Why are you here
when I didn't even call you?

316
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:45,667
It's about the competition day.

317
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:48,467
I wanted to ask if the Chairman
would be part of the judging panel.

318
00:17:49,207 --> 00:17:52,305
How could he judge in his condition?

319
00:17:52,305 --> 00:17:54,640
The executives and I will handle it.

320
00:17:54,942 --> 00:17:56,409
Did the Chairman approve that?

321
00:17:57,167 --> 00:17:59,367
That's my decision to make.

322
00:17:59,367 --> 00:18:01,948
I'm the CEO of Kangsu Construction,
the next Chairman!

323
00:18:01,948 --> 00:18:03,816
Still, you should check his opinion.

324
00:18:06,833 --> 00:18:09,921
But are you confident?

325
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:11,233
What's your basis?

326
00:18:11,433 --> 00:18:12,658
You'll see on the day.

327
00:18:17,426 --> 00:18:20,265
He has really grown up.

328
00:18:27,900 --> 00:18:29,600
Why do you keep following us?

329
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:30,600
Sorry?

330
00:18:31,173 --> 00:18:35,814
In case the wind makes you cough again,
I prepared these.

331
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,515
There's barely any wind.

332
00:18:37,933 --> 00:18:38,933
Don't worry, and go inside.

333
00:18:38,933 --> 00:18:40,152
No, it's all right.

334
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:44,094
If you get thirsty during your walk,
just let me know.

335
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,400
I've brought a drink too.

336
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,200
No outside schedule today?

337
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,133
Even if there is, there isn't.

338
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:53,342
My job today is to attend to you both.

339
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:57,002
You look so lovely today, Mother.

340
00:18:57,687 --> 00:18:58,920
- The color suits you well.
- What?

341
00:18:59,271 --> 00:19:01,637
What is this situation now?

342
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:07,813
Out for some fresh air, Chairman?

343
00:19:08,086 --> 00:19:11,120
The daffodils are in full bloom.
Would you like to see them?

344
00:19:11,467 --> 00:19:12,467
Shall we?

345
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:13,685
I'll support you.

346
00:19:13,956 --> 00:19:16,522
I won't tell him,
so don't worry and go inside.

347
00:19:17,219 --> 00:19:19,019
He might get suspicious otherwise.

348
00:19:19,019 --> 00:19:20,019
Sorry?

349
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,895
Then I'll trust you, Mother.

350
00:19:23,533 --> 00:19:25,631
Thank you, Mother.

351
00:19:34,407 --> 00:19:36,976
There must be something big going on.

352
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:38,733
Just wait.

353
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:42,700
I'll uncover every secret
in this family somehow.

354
00:19:43,299 --> 00:19:45,784
I'm Eun Su Jeong.

355
00:19:46,073 --> 00:19:47,173
Silver Crystal.

356
00:19:56,033 --> 00:19:57,033
Hey, Cho Rong.

357
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,500
What? Mom...

358
00:20:00,053 --> 00:20:01,520
I'm sorry. Please excuse me.

359
00:20:07,527 --> 00:20:08,941
I'll head out first.

360
00:20:09,227 --> 00:20:10,593
Yes, see you tomorrow.

361
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:18,159
Yes, Dad.
I'll come home right after I'm done.

362
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,886
Are you heading home?

363
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:22,955
Have a safe trip.

364
00:20:23,466 --> 00:20:24,466
By the way...

365
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:26,792
I enjoyed the porridge.

366
00:20:27,306 --> 00:20:29,506
Sorry? Okay...

367
00:20:34,567 --> 00:20:36,335
I told him not to say anything.

368
00:20:41,103 --> 00:20:42,189
Honey.

369
00:20:42,189 --> 00:20:43,243
Go to the room.

370
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:44,287
Wait a second.

371
00:20:44,287 --> 00:20:45,311
Go to the room.

372
00:20:46,707 --> 00:20:48,881
Sit here, I have something to say.

373
00:20:50,247 --> 00:20:52,267
Let's talk tomorrow morning
after you sober up.

374
00:20:52,267 --> 00:20:53,333
No.

375
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:56,255
I want to say it now. I must.

376
00:20:59,006 --> 00:21:01,961
All right, go ahead. What is it?

377
00:21:04,180 --> 00:21:06,632
I'm fine.

378
00:21:07,293 --> 00:21:09,668
I don't need the kids.

379
00:21:10,386 --> 00:21:13,205
Now, I only need one person,

380
00:21:13,947 --> 00:21:16,109
just you.

381
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:20,000
All right, I get it.
Go lie down in your room.

382
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,134
Okay.

383
00:21:23,054 --> 00:21:24,387
Mom, what happened?

384
00:21:24,853 --> 00:21:26,819
Hey, my daughter!

385
00:21:27,149 --> 00:21:29,387
I was in a really good mood,

386
00:21:29,387 --> 00:21:32,513
so I just had one drink
with Cho Rong's grandma.

387
00:21:33,326 --> 00:21:35,494
That doesn't look like just one drink.

388
00:21:36,307 --> 00:21:38,864
That's good.
I'll make you some honey water.

389
00:21:43,833 --> 00:21:45,137
Who is this?

390
00:21:46,120 --> 00:21:48,875
Dr. Cho.

391
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:52,711
No, the web novel author.

392
00:21:53,213 --> 00:21:54,213
Mom.

393
00:21:54,533 --> 00:21:55,567
Cho Eun Nim.

394
00:21:57,006 --> 00:21:58,589
I feel wronged.

395
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,988
I never pushed you to go to med school.

396
00:22:03,867 --> 00:22:06,969
You were the one who studied well
and got in,

397
00:22:07,700 --> 00:22:11,528
so I just believed you'd become a doctor.

398
00:22:11,867 --> 00:22:14,099
That's why I called you "Dr. Cho."

399
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,670
Did that pressure you that much?

400
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:20,067
I'm sorry, Mom.

401
00:22:20,792 --> 00:22:23,676
It's my fault for not believing...

402
00:22:23,676 --> 00:22:25,978
you'd understand if I were honest.
I'm sorry.

403
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:27,666
No.

404
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,117
It's all my fault.

405
00:22:32,686 --> 00:22:33,752
My fault.

406
00:22:37,267 --> 00:22:39,224
And from now on,

407
00:22:40,634 --> 00:22:42,795
I'm going to live my own life.

408
00:22:44,393 --> 00:22:48,000
I will live my life properly now,

409
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:52,638
going from a life without me
to one with me in it.

410
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:57,409
Yes, Mom. Please do.

411
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:00,667
I have a dream...

412
00:23:01,786 --> 00:23:05,386
I've never told anyone about.

413
00:23:06,633 --> 00:23:10,856
I'm going to achieve it.

414
00:23:12,147 --> 00:23:13,494
What is it?

415
00:23:15,380 --> 00:23:18,297
I want to go to college.

416
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,968
I always wanted to study so badly,

417
00:23:24,500 --> 00:23:25,837
but back then, the circumstances...

418
00:23:28,770 --> 00:23:31,267
I worked at a factory during the day...

419
00:23:31,267 --> 00:23:34,212
and barely finished night school.

420
00:23:34,787 --> 00:23:37,583
But I met your father,

421
00:23:37,583 --> 00:23:40,067
and my life improved.

422
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:41,500
Honey.

423
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:45,024
After raising all of you,

424
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:48,694
I thought I'd finally pursue that dream,

425
00:23:50,353 --> 00:23:52,664
but time just slipped by.

426
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:59,371
Honey, can I go to college now?

427
00:24:00,413 --> 00:24:01,707
Right?

428
00:24:02,113 --> 00:24:06,311
Of course you can.

429
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,747
Of course, Mom.

430
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:13,018
If you set your mind to it, you'll do it.

431
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,600
Drink this, Mom.

432
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,757
Drink this
and let's make that dream happen.

433
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:35,774
Mom.

434
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,000
I'm sorry, honey.

435
00:24:45,967 --> 00:24:47,333
I won't lie anymore.

436
00:24:49,733 --> 00:24:52,958
Just give me a little more time.

437
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,101
Can I sleep with you tonight?

438
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,037
Of course. Come here.

439
00:25:11,626 --> 00:25:13,278
I have a question.

440
00:25:13,533 --> 00:25:16,133
Do you only love Dad
because he's a professor?

441
00:25:17,353 --> 00:25:19,767
Even if he wasn't,

442
00:25:19,767 --> 00:25:21,633
he'd still be the best dad to me.

443
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,056
Can you feel the same way?

444
00:25:25,886 --> 00:25:27,392
I understand.

445
00:25:28,434 --> 00:25:29,895
I'll think about it.

446
00:25:31,399 --> 00:25:32,464
Go to sleep.

447
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:49,781
You're still awake?

448
00:25:52,046 --> 00:25:54,987
I'm going to trust you one more time.

449
00:25:55,789 --> 00:25:56,789
What?

450
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,592
Harvard campus or writing institute,
it doesn't matter.

451
00:26:02,026 --> 00:26:04,830
But don't give up
on teaching at a university.

452
00:26:05,833 --> 00:26:07,593
Of course not. I won't give up.

453
00:26:07,593 --> 00:26:09,407
You didn't earn a PhD
from Hanguk University...

454
00:26:09,407 --> 00:26:11,870
just to teach at a local cram school.

455
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:15,340
Promise me you'll find a way...

456
00:26:15,967 --> 00:26:18,009
to stand at a university podium again.

457
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:19,945
I will. I promise.

458
00:26:21,267 --> 00:26:22,848
Go sleep in Bit Na's room.

459
00:26:23,533 --> 00:26:25,267
Why are you on the sofa?

460
00:26:26,007 --> 00:26:27,007
I'm fine.

461
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:31,523
I'm just grateful
you gave me another chance.

462
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:44,937
(Expert opinion requested,
Same person as in the photo)

463
00:26:52,114 --> 00:26:54,945
Yes, Chairman. The results are in.

464
00:26:56,233 --> 00:26:58,634
Yes, I'll come see you shortly.

465
00:27:37,567 --> 00:27:38,567
No...

466
00:28:01,813 --> 00:28:04,816
(Our Happy Days)

467
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:08,420
I accepted the internship to get Joy back,

468
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:09,455
but not anymore.

469
00:28:09,455 --> 00:28:11,056
I'm confident I can win.

470
00:28:11,056 --> 00:28:13,425
Let's both do our best
in our own positions.

471
00:28:13,580 --> 00:28:16,161
What does it take to win someone's heart?

472
00:28:16,161 --> 00:28:17,930
Why do you hate me so much?

473
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:19,100
Seriously!

474
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:21,167
Did you really go through with it?

475
00:28:21,167 --> 00:28:22,667
What are you talking about?

476
00:28:22,667 --> 00:28:24,035
Bring it to me right now!

477
00:28:24,670 --> 00:28:26,538
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
